title: BANNING: 17-year-old reports being stabbed by two men
text:
By BRIAN ROKOS / STAFF WRITER
Published: Oct. 5, 2015 Updated: 12:17 p.m. BANNING: 17-year-old reports being stabbed by two men Print Photo Share Pin It More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT Related article Â» Do you know about this incident? Anyone with information on the stabbing report is asked to contact the Banning Police Department at 951-849-1771.
A 17-year-old said he was stabbed by two men in Banning on Saturday, Oct. 3, and police are searching for the attackers.
The teen reported that he was stabbed several times about 10 a.m. in the 1100 block of W. Gilman Street, a Banning Police Department news release said Monday.
The victim was taken to Desert Regional Medical Center in Palm Springs.
The circumstances surrounding the stabbing are still under investigation. Anyone with information is asked to contact the Banning Police Department at 951-849-1771.
